{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738258992,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_gUAoVdiKHzGmyvpOK4WrdKZv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"pre-commit|precommit|Comment Hygiene|comment hygiene","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 764 matches (showing first 100)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/integration/prompts/iteration-005.md:\n  Line 11: THIS ITERATION IS THE OPERATOR'S CO-#1 PRIORITY: AUTOMATION. The guiding principle: NO manual steps. Every behavior should fire automatically from an existing surface (on-write hook, scheduled sweep, startup, /doctor, pre-commit) and be self-maintaining.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/integration/prompts/iteration-003.md:\n  Line 13: - HOOKS / automation surfaces (emphasize these): .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/mutation-hooks.ts, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/, plus any startup / skill-advisor / pre-commit hooks you can find.\n\n  Line 20: Item -> automatic trigger (on-write hook / scheduled sweep / startup / /doctor / pre-commit) -> surface. This is the most important section — most of the UX/automation lives here.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/integration/deep-research-strategy.md:\n  Line 27: - [ ] 003 Impact on COMMANDS + AGENTS + HOOKS: /memory:* /speckit:* /doctor; @context/@orchestrate/@markdown; skill-advisor hook, startup hook, pre-commit, mutation-hooks.ts (the aut