l — it relies entirely on the `BeforeAgent` constitutional injection and the pre-commit gate as a fallback. Copilot's prompt hook is NEXT-PROMPT freshness (current prompt sees prior turn's brief), which is architecturally different from Claude's in-turn injection. The shared-payload parity claim (section 10, line 121) is narrower than full hook parity: all runtimes *can* receive the same startup brief, but the transport mechanism and freshness semantics differ materially. The `session-cleanup.sh` script (line 4036) was generalized to handle all four runtimes, but only Claude and OpenCode actually *invoke* it via a Stop hook.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-and-program-cleanup/012-comprehensive-deep-review-audit/006-governance-skdoc-skcode/review/lineages/codex-1/resource-map.md:\n  Line 14: - `.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit`: F002, client-side bypass surface.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/008-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-016.md:\n  Line 290: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n  Line 3590: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/handover.md:155:WHY). The new `.cjs` files (fanout-pool/fanout-merge/fanout-run) must comply — the pre-commit + write-time\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/008-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-015.md:\n  Line 68: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n  Line 6879: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/handover.md:155:WHY). The new `.cjs` files (fanout-pool/fanout-merge/fanout-run) must comply — the pre-commit + write-time\n\n  Line 12552: .o