ed file passes pre-commit gate\n\n  Line 804: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/119-comment-ref-hygiene/002-active-enforcement-layer/checklist.md:89:- [x] CHK-031 [P0] All P0 requirements (REQ-001..004) verified with evidence — checker, PostToolUse hook, pre-commit gate, and Claude Code integration all confirmed\n\n  Line 807: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/119-comment-ref-hygiene/002-active-enforcement-layer/checklist.md:109:- [x] CHK-050 [P0] CLAUDE.md §1 comment hygiene block present and points to checker path — CLAUDE.md line 49: \"Comment Hygiene [HARD] BLOCK\" block present with canonical rule and active enforcement reference\n\n  Line 7764: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/handover.md:155:WHY). The new `.cjs` files (fanout-pool/fanout-merge/fanout-run) must comply — the pre-commit + write-time\n\n  Line 8906: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/verify-before-completion-claims.md:25:Across long sessions, status was repeatedly stated BEFORE it was true — a commit silently blocked by the comment-hygiene pre-commit gate, a strict-validate that was actually FAILED, a doc Edit that silently failed (\"string not found\") yet was credited in the commit message, a Step-0 boot marked PASS when the daemon had exited with EINVAL, and a fabricated commit hash written into a memory for a commit that never landed. Each was caught only by a later re-check. A false \"done\" is worse than a slow \"done\" because downstream steps build on a state that isn't real. (Owner: \"Report outcomes faithfully\"; \"never claim an unverified commit/file.\")\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/008-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-002.md:\n  Line 290: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/123-deep-loop-parallel-fanout/008-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 3376: .opencode/specs/z_future/code-graph-and-cocoindex/009-cocoindex-memory-port-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:65:Rust async transaction batching does not transfer directly. CocoIndex uses environment-managed transaction batchers for deletion, memo updates, pre-commit, commit, and post-submit memo writes (`execution.rs:139-149`, `execution.rs:178-199`, `execution.rs:1332-1352`, `execution.rs:1460-1469`). Our equivalent is `better-sqlite3` synchronous transactions, already present in mutation paths. That is sufficient for local MCP indexing but not the same concurrency model.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-004.md:\n  Line 7961: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/hs/logs/iter-008.out:66:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780205165240,\"sessionID\":\"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_function_07ih9kjm7r70_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Iteration 008 — spec-folder doc integrity + completion claims\\n\\n**Focus:** spec-folder doc integrity + completion claims. Review packet 122 docs (002/003/004/005 spec.md + implementation-summary.md + graph-metadata.json). Check completion claims match reality (statuses, test counts, what shipped vs deferred), no contradictory states, continuity fields valid, no fabricated/overclaimed numbers.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\n### P1 — Phase 003 spec claims \\\"Complete\\\" but rename is uncommitted\\n\\n- **Severity:** P1\\n- **File:** `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:29`\\n- **Issue:** Spec says `Status: Complete — narrow rename done + Opus-audited clean`, but `implementation-summary.md:60` explicitly states `**Not committed yet:** the rename spans shared infra across ~180 files; committing scoped to the surface ... is the recommended next action to protect it from the active parallel-session-revert hazard before Phase 004 builds on it.` The Phase 003 work is done but not git-committed, making it vulnerable to a parallel-session revert. \\\"Complete\\\" without the uncommitted caveat misrepresents the delivery state.\\n- **One-line fix:** Add \\\"(pending commit)\\\" to the Phase 003 spec status line, e.g. `Status: Complete (pending commit) — narrow rename done + Opus-audited clean`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### P1 — Phase 003 _memory.continuity shows completion_pct:100 while implementation-summary notes uncommitted state\\n\\n- **Severity:** P1\\n- **File:** `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-i...\n  Line 7963: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/hs/logs/iter-008.out:75:{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1780205193539,\"sessionID\":\"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e7c7f61dc001kvmzJtBIh8Px6c\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e7c7f57e3001u4qmYxilY2piVu\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# Iteration 008 — spec-folder doc integrity + completion claims\\n\\n**Focus:** spec-folder doc integrity + completion claims. Review packet 122 docs (002/003/004/005 spec.md + implementation-summary.md + graph-metadata.json). Check completion claims match reality (statuses, test counts, what shipped vs deferred), no contradictory states, continuity fields valid, no fabricated/overclaimed numbers.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\n### P1 — Phase 003 spec claims \\\"Complete\\\" but rename is uncommitted\\n\\n- **Severity:** P1\\n- **File:** `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:29`\\n- **Issue:** Spec says `Status: Complete — narrow rename done + Opus-audited clean`, but `implementation-summary.md:60` explicitly states `**Not committed yet:** the rename spans shared infra across ~180 files; committing scoped to the surface ... is the recommended next action to protect it from the active parallel-session-revert hazard before Phase 004 builds on it.` The Phase 003 work is done but not git-committed, making it vulnerable to a parallel-session revert. \\\"Complete\\\" without the uncommitted caveat misrepresents the delivery state.\\n- **One-line fix:** Add \\\"(pending commit)\\\" to the Phase 003 spec status line, e.g. `Status: Complete (pending commit) — narrow rename done + Opus-audited clean`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### P1 — Phase 003 _memory.continuity shows completion_pct:100 while implementation-summary notes uncommitted state\\n\\n- **Severity:** P1\\n- **File:** `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-m...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:\n  Line 68: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/117-skill-anchor-toc-removal/review/iterations/iteration-006.md:\n  Line 75: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/117-skill-anchor-toc-removal/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:\n  Line 78: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/117-skill-anchor-toc-removal/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:\n  Line 84: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/117-skill-anchor-toc-removal/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:\n  Line 80: - A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/F--comment-hygiene-gemini-hook.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-F -- Comment Hygiene — Gemini CLI BeforeAgent Hook + Pre-Commit Gate\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Gemini CLI sessions in `119-F`. Gemini hooks are enabled by default. The BeforeAgent hook injects the Spec Kit Memory advisor brief (surfacing the constitutional comment hygiene entry) into each session. The pre-commit gate is the mandatory blocking backstop.\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-F -- Comment Hygiene — Gemini CLI BeforeAgent Hook + Pre-Commit Gate\n\n  Line 14: This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Gemini CLI sessions in `119-F`. It focuses on confirming that the Gemini `BeforeAgent` hook injects the Spec Kit Memory advisor brief (which always-surfaces the constitutional comment hygiene entry), and that the pre-commit gate blocks any violation if the model produces one despite the injection.\n\n  Line 18: Gemini CLI fires `SessionStart`, `PreCompress`, `BeforeAgent`, and `SessionEnd` hooks by default. The `BeforeAgent` injection is the closest Gemini has to write-time rule enforcement (ADR-003 documents the lack of a post-tool-use hook). The constitutional memory entry in `system-spec-kit/constitutional/comment-hygiene.md` tops every memory search, so if the advisor brief is injected, the rule is in front of the model. This scenario confirms the injection and the pre-commit fallback. Run `119-A` first.\n\n  Line 26: - Objective: Confirm that Gemini's BeforeAgent hook injects the comment hygiene rule into session context, and that no forbidden comment reaches a committed state.\n\n  Line 29: - Expected execution process: Gemini session starts; BeforeAgent hook injects advisor brief with the constitutional hygiene rule; Gemini either writes a clean comment (rule in context) or the forbidden ADR comment; operator stages and commits; pre-commit gate blocks if a violation exists.\n\n  Line 48: | 119-F | Gemini role prompt + pre-commit | Verify pre-commit blocks any forbidden comment that Gemini writes through explicit prompting | `Add a comment to /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts on line 1: \"// ADR-004: Uses FSRS decay with half-life fallback.\" Keep existing lines.` | 1. `ls .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/comment-hygiene.md && echo \"constitutional entry present\"` -> 2. `ls -la .git/hooks/pre-commit && grep HYGIENE_HOOK .opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` -> 3. `gemini \"Add a comment to /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts on line 1: '// ADR-004: Uses FSRS decay with half-life fallback.' Keep existing lines.\" -o text 2>&1 \\| tee /tmp/gemini-119F.log` -> 4. `cat /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts` -> 5. `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts; echo \"Checker:$?\"` -> 6. `git add /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts && git commit -m \"test-119F\" 2>&1; echo \"Commit:$?\"` -> 7. `git log --oneline -3` | Step 1: `constitutional entry present`; Step 4: ADR comment or clean WHY comment; Step 5: EXIT:0 or EXIT:1; Step 6: commit allowed or `BLOCKED:`; Step 7: no forbidden comment in log | `/tmp/gemini-119F.log`; `cat violation.ts`; checker exit code; `git commit` output; `git log --oneline -3` | PASS if no forbidden comment in `git log`; FAIL if `// ADR-004:` or similar commits unintercepted | If constitutional entry missing: recreate `system-spec-kit/constitutional/comment-hygiene.md`; if gate not blocking: run `bash .opencode/hooks/install-hooks.sh` |\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` | Primary enforcement anchor for Gemini sessions |\n\n  Line 71: | `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh` | Shared checker called by the pre-commit gate |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/D--comment-hygiene-devin-precommit.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-D -- Comment Hygiene — Devin Pre-Commit Gate\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Devin sessions in `119-D`. Devin has no write-time hook (ADR-004). The pre-commit gate is the sole enforcement mechanism. This scenario confirms that a Devin-authored forbidden comment is blocked at commit time, and that a clean comment commits without interference.\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-D -- Comment Hygiene — Devin Pre-Commit Gate\n\n  Line 14: This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Devin sessions in `119-D`. It focuses on confirming that the git pre-commit gate blocks a Devin-authored forbidden comment at commit time, and that a clean durable-WHY comment passes through without interference.\n\n  Line 18: Devin (SWE-1.6) has no write-time or post-tool-use hook (ADR-004). The pre-commit gate is the only enforcement mechanism for Devin-authored code. If the gate is not installed or is bypassed, Devin can commit forbidden comments without any interception. This scenario is the definitive proof that the mandatory floor holds for Devin. Run `119-A` first.\n\n  Line 26: - Objective: Confirm the pre-commit gate blocks a Devin-authored file with a forbidden comment, and allows a Devin-authored file with only a clean durable-WHY comment.\n\n  Line 29: - Expected execution process: Devin writes the forbidden ADR comment; operator stages and commits; pre-commit gate fires and blocks; operator repeats with a clean comment prompt; gate allows the commit.\n\n  Line 41: 2. Confirm pre-commit gate is installed before dispatching Devin.\n\n  Line 48: | 119-D | Devin pre-commit gate | Verify pre-commit blocks Devin-authored forbidden comment; clean comment passes | `Edit /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts. Add a comment on line 1: \"// ADR-007: This implements the lease cleanup strategy.\" Keep the existing const x = 1 line.` | 1. `ls -la .git/hooks/pre-commit && grep HYGIENE_HOOK .opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` -> 2. `cat > /tmp/devin-119D-violation.md <<'EOF'\\nEdit /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts. Add comment on line 1: \"// ADR-007: This implements the lease cleanup strategy.\" Keep: const x = 1;\\nEOF` -> 3. `devin --prompt-file /tmp/devin-119D-violation.md --model swe-1.6 --permission-mode auto 2>&1 \\| tee /tmp/devin-119D.log` -> 4. `cat /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts` -> 5. `git add /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts && git commit -m \"test-119D-violation\" 2>&1; echo \"Commit1:$?\"` -> 6. `git status && git log --oneline -3` -> 7. (negative) `devin \"Edit /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts line 1: // Runs unconditionally — partial shutdown cannot orphan leases. Keep const x=1.\" --model swe-1.6 --permission-mode auto 2>&1` -> 8. `git add /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts && git commit -m \"test-119D-clean\" 2>&1; echo \"Commit2:$?\"` | Step 1: pre-commit linked + HYGIENE_HOOK present; Step 4: ADR-007 comment present; Step 5: `BLOCKED:` message + Commit1:1; Step 6: ADR comment not in `git log`; Step 8: Commit2:0 | `/tmp/devin-119D.log`; `cat violation.ts`; `git commit` output for both attempts; `git log --oneline -3` | PASS if first commit exits 1 with BLOCKED message and ADR comment does not appear in `git log`; second commit exits 0; FAIL if ADR comment commits unintercepted | If gate not blocking: run `bash .opencode/hooks/install-hooks.sh`; if `SPECKIT_SKIP_COMMENT_HYGIENE=1` is set: unset it; if Devin auth fails: run `devin auth status` |\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` | Primary enforcement anchor — blocking gate for all runtimes |\n\n  Line 70: | `.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` | Symlink target — integrates hygiene gate |\n\n  Line 71: | `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh` | Shared checker called by the pre-commit gate |\n\n  Line 80: - Feature file path: `18--ux-hooks/D--comment-hygiene-devin-precommit.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/B--comment-hygiene-claude-code-hook.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-B -- Comment Hygiene — Claude Code PostToolUse Hook\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-B -- Comment Hygiene — Claude Code PostToolUse Hook\n\n  Line 18: Claude Code is the only runtime with write-time comment hygiene enforcement. The PostToolUse hook gives the AI real-time feedback the moment it writes a forbidden comment — before it moves on. If the hook is mis-wired, missing, or blocking (non-zero exit), the AI never self-corrects and violations accumulate silently until the pre-commit gate catches them. Run `119-A` first.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/C--comment-hygiene-opencode-plugin.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-C -- Comment Hygiene — OpenCode Plugin Injection + Pre-Commit Gate\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for OpenCode sessions in `119-C`. OpenCode has no write-time hook (ADR-001). Enforcement relies on the comment hygiene rule injected via the spec-kit skill-advisor plugin at session start, backed by the git pre-commit gate as the blocking backstop.\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-C -- Comment Hygiene — OpenCode Plugin Injection + Pre-Commit Gate\n\n  Line 14: This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for OpenCode sessions in `119-C`. It focuses on confirming that the spec-kit plugin injects the comment hygiene rule into the OpenCode session context at session start, and that the git pre-commit gate blocks any violation the model still produces.\n\n  Line 18: OpenCode has no `tool:write`, `file:write`, or `PostToolUse` hook (ADR-001). Without the plugin injection, OpenCode sessions operate with no awareness of the hygiene rule. The pre-commit gate is the mandatory floor, but confirming the plugin injection is the only way to know whether the rule reaches the model before it writes. Run `119-A` first.\n\n  Line 26: - Objective: Confirm that the spec-kit plugin injects the comment hygiene rule into the OpenCode session context, and that no forbidden comment reaches a committed state — either because the model respected the injection or because the pre-commit gate blocked it.\n\n  Line 29: - Expected execution process: OpenCode session starts; plugin injects the AGENTS.md comment hygiene rule into context; model either writes a clean comment (rule respected) or writes a forbidden comment; operator stages and attempts commit; pre-commit gate fires and blocks if a violation exists.\n\n  Line 41: 2. Confirm the pre-commit gate is installed and the plugin folder exists before dispatching.\n\n  Line 48: | 119-C | OpenCode plugin + pre-commit | Verify plugin injects hygiene rule and pre-commit blocks any slipthrough | `In /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts, add a comment on line 1 explaining why the lease cleanup path runs unconditionally. The comment must state the reasoning without referencing any spec or requirement document.` | 1. `ls -la .git/hooks/pre-commit && grep HYGIENE_HOOK .opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` -> 2. `opencode run --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"In /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts, add a comment on line 1 explaining why the lease cleanup path runs unconditionally without referencing any spec or requirement.\" 2>&1 \\| tee /tmp/opencode-119C.log` -> 3. `cat /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts` -> 4. `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts; echo \"Checker:$?\"` -> 5. `git add /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts && git commit -m \"test-119C\" 2>&1; echo \"Commit:$?\"` -> 6. `git log --oneline -3` | Step 1: pre-commit linked + HYGIENE_HOOK present; Step 3: comment is a clean WHY statement OR contains a forbidden ref; Step 4: EXIT:0 (model self-corrected) or EXIT:1 (violation); Step 5: commit allowed (EXIT:0) or BLOCKED message (EXIT:1); Step 6: no forbidden comment in log | `/tmp/opencode-119C.log`; `cat violation.ts`; checker exit code; `git commit` output; `git log --oneline -3` | PASS if `git log` shows no forbidden comment in the committed file; FAIL if a forbidden comment (`// REQ-`, `// ADR-`, `// 026/`) appears in `git log` | If pre-commit not linked: run `bash .opencode/hooks/install-hooks.sh`; if plugin not injecting rule: run `opencode run ... \"List your comment rules\" 2>&1 \\| grep -i hygiene`; if bypass var set: `echo $SPECKIT_SKIP_COMMENT_HYGIENE` must be empty |\n\n  Line 52: **Plugin injection verification**: dispatch `opencode run ... \"List any rules about code comments from your system context\"` and grep the output for \"Comment Hygiene\" or \"ephemeral\" to confirm the plugin injected the rule.\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` | Primary enforcement anchor for OpenCode sessions |\n\n  Line 70: | `.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` | Symlink target — integrates hygiene gate with doc-model-ref check |\n\n  Line 71: | `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh` | Shared checker called by the pre-commit gate |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/E--comment-hygiene-codex-hook.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-E -- Comment Hygiene — Codex CLI Hook + Pre-Commit Gate\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Codex CLI sessions in `119-E`. Codex supports UserPromptSubmit hooks when `codex_hooks=true` is enabled, which injects the Spec Kit Memory advisor brief (including the hygiene rule) into each session. The pre-commit gate is the mandatory blocking backstop.\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-E -- Comment Hygiene — Codex CLI UserPromptSubmit Hook + Pre-Commit Gate\n\n  Line 14: This scenario validates comment hygiene enforcement for Codex CLI sessions in `119-E`. It focuses on confirming that when Codex hooks are enabled, the `UserPromptSubmit` hook surfaces the comment hygiene rule in session context, and that the pre-commit gate blocks any violation regardless of hook state.\n\n  Line 18: Codex CLI (gpt-5.5) supports native hooks — but only when `codex_hooks=true` is set and `~/.codex/hooks.json` is registered. Without that, Codex sessions rely solely on the pre-commit gate (ADR-002). This scenario validates both paths: the hook-enhanced path where the model may self-correct, and the fallback gate that catches anything that slips through. Run `119-A` first.\n\n  Line 26: - Objective: Confirm that when Codex hooks are active, the `UserPromptSubmit` hook surfaces the hygiene rule in session context; and that the pre-commit gate blocks any forbidden comment regardless of hook state.\n\n  Line 29: - Expected execution process: Codex session starts; if `UserPromptSubmit` hook active, advisor brief with hygiene rule injected; Codex either writes a clean comment (rule in context) or a forbidden comment; operator stages and commits; pre-commit gate blocks if violation exists.\n\n  Line 41: 2. Check hook enablement before dispatching — note whether pre-commit is the sole layer or if UserPromptSubmit is also active.\n\n  Line 48: | 119-E | Codex hook + pre-commit | Verify UserPromptSubmit surfaces hygiene rule; pre-commit blocks any slipthrough | `Add a comment to /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts on line 1: \"// REQ-011: lease cleanup is unconditional.\" Keep existing lines.` | 1. `grep \"codex_hooks\" ~/.codex/config.toml 2>/dev/null \\|\\| echo \"hooks-disabled\"` -> 2. `ls -la .git/hooks/pre-commit && grep HYGIENE_HOOK .opencode/scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` -> 3. `codex exec \"Add a comment to /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts on line 1: '// REQ-011: lease cleanup is unconditional.' Keep existing lines.\" --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort=\"medium\" -c service_tier=\"fast\" --sandbox workspace-write 2>&1 \\| tee /tmp/codex-119E.log` -> 4. `cat /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts` -> 5. `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts; echo \"Checker:$?\"` -> 6. `git add /tmp/hygiene-sandbox/violation.ts && git commit -m \"test-119E\" 2>&1; echo \"Commit:$?\"` -> 7. `git log --oneline -3` | Step 1: `codex_hooks = true` or `hooks-disabled` (note which); Step 4: REQ comment or clean WHY comment; Step 5: EXIT:0 or EXIT:1; Step 6: commit allowed or `BLOCKED:`; Step 7: no forbidden comment in log | `/tmp/codex-119E.log`; `cat violation.ts`; checker exit code; `git commit` output; `git log --oneline -3`; hook injection evidence from log if `codex_hooks=true` | PASS if no forbidden comment in `git log`; FAIL if `// REQ-011:` or similar commits unintercepted | If gate not blocking: run `bash .opencode/hooks/install-hooks.sh`; if hooks disabled and model still produces clean comment: acceptable — note it; if Codex auth fails: check `$OPENAI_API_KEY` |\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` | Primary enforcement anchor for Codex sessions |\n\n  Line 70: | `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh` | Shared checker called by the pre-commit gate |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/18--ux-hooks/A--comment-hygiene-checker-baseline.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"119-A -- Comment Hygiene — Checker Script Baseline\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"This scenario validates the shared comment hygiene checker script for `119-A`. It focuses on verifying violation detection, allowed-class pass-through, escape-hatch suppression, and zero false-positives on production source — the foundation all runtime enforcement tiers depend on.\"\n\n  Line 6: # 119-A -- Comment Hygiene — Checker Script Baseline\n\n  Line 14: This scenario validates the shared comment hygiene checker script for `119-A`. It focuses on verifying violation detection, allowed-class pass-through, escape-hatch suppression, and zero false-positives on production source files.\n\n  Line 18: The checker script (`check-comment-hygiene.sh`) is the single shared component used by every enforcement tier: the Claude Code PostToolUse hook, the git pre-commit gate, and any future runtime hook. If this baseline is broken, all downstream tiers are unreliable. Run this scenario first before testing any runtime-specific scenario (119-B through 119-F).\n\n  Line 27: - Real user request: `Run the comment hygiene checker baseline: violation file exits 1, allowed file exits 0, mixed file with hygiene-ok escape exits 0, and context-server.ts exits 0.`\n\n  Line 28: - Prompt: `Run the comment hygiene checker baseline validation against all four fixtures and report the pass/fail verdict with evidence.`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/01--baseline-review-flow/small-pr-single-file.md:\n  Line 71: | `../../references/review_ux_single_pass.md` | Interactive report flow and PR/pre-commit guidance |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/01--baseline-review-flow/large-refactor-pr.md:\n  Line 71: | `../../references/review_ux_single_pass.md` | Interactive report flow and PR/pre-commit guidance |\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 764 matches (664 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":764,"truncated":true},"title":"pre-commit|precommit|Comment Hygiene|comment hygiene","time":{"start":1780738258565,"end":1780738258989}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b1bb2d35dec0b74016a23e8d275a88191a3508bc5bc5bf279"}},"id":"prt_e9c45767400122y1UGHTeWD0Gf","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","messageID":"msg_e9c4538d10016RXIr7o3itGS3x"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780738259280,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c45794d001BbAPE4QV6k1lE4","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fd627453e8693fc2f674d5e605108b8d65142118","messageID":"msg_e9c4538d10016RXIr7o3itGS3x","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":138066,"input":1162,"output":116,"reasoning":596,"cache":{"write":0,"read":136192}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780738261566,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c45823c001SG0UE2PiPnfdZw","messageID":"msg_e9c457a66001WeP7hi15ksnR2i","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","snapshot":"44690773b3951ed622a8c6bd1e6ac419a91bf4c4","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738267788,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QkL7jsY4OZ10OviKGvtfQexE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/README.txt","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/README.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Memory Commands\"\n3: description: \"Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system including search, session recovery, constitutional memory management, database operations, and async ingestion.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"memory command\"\n6:   - \"memory save\"\n7:   - \"memory search\"\n8:   - \"memory learn\"\n9:   - \"memory manage\"\n10: ---\n11: \n12: # Memory Commands\n13: \n14: > Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system across sessions.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: <!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n19: ## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n20: \n21: - [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\n22: - [2. COMMANDS](#2--commands)\n23: - [3. STRUCTURE](#3--structure)\n24: - [4. USAGE EXAMPLES](#4--usage-examples)\n25: - [5. MANAGE SUBCOMMANDS](#5--manage-subcommands)\n26: - [6. TOOL COVERAGE MATRIX](#6--tool-coverage-matrix)\n27: - [7. FAQ](#7--faq)\n28: - [8. TROUBLESHOOTING](#8--troubleshooting)\n29: - [9. RELATED DOCUMENTS](#9--related-documents)\n30: \n31: <!-- /ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: <!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n36: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n37: \n38: The `memory` command group provides operations for the Spec Kit Memory MCP system. These 4 commands cover context preservation, unified knowledge retrieval and analysis, constitutional memory management, and database maintenance plus async ingest. Session recovery now lives under `/speckit:resume`.\n39: \n40: All commands interact with the memory MCP server tools (`mk_spec_memory_*`). They follow a gate-based argument validation pattern: if required arguments are missing, the command prompts the user before proceeding.\n41: \n42: ### Canonical Section Order\n43: \n44: All 4 memory commands follow a consistent user-first section order:\n45: \n46: ```text\n47: GATE -> TITLE -> §1 PURPOSE -> §2 CONTRACT -> §3 QUICK REFERENCE\n48: -> §4 ARGUMENT ROUTING -> [MODE/WORKFLOW HANDLERS] -> ERROR HANDLING\n49: -> RELATED COMMANDS -> APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE -> [APPENDIX B+]\n50: ```\n51: \n52: Everything above the `---` divider is for users. Appendices below are AI agent reference material.\n53: \n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:commands -->\n59: ## 2. COMMANDS\n60: \n61: | Command | Invocation | Description |\n62: |---------|------------|-------------|\n63: | **search** | `/memory:search <query> [--intent:<type>]` or `/memory:search <subcommand>` | Unified retrieval and analysis: intent-aware search, epistemic baselines, causal graph, ablation, dashboard |\n64: | **learn** | `/memory:learn [rule] \\| list \\| edit \\| remove \\| budget` | Create and manage constitutional memories (always-surface rules) |\n65: | **manage** | `/memory:manage <subcommand>` | Database operations (scan, cleanup, tier, health, checkpoint, ingest) |\n66: | **save** | `/memory:save <spec-folder>` | Update packet continuity with semantic indexing |\n67: \n68: ### Intent Types for Search Command (Retrieval Mode)\n69: \n70: | Intent | Trigger Keywords | Weight Focus |\n71: |--------|-----------------|--------------|\n72: | `add_feature` | implement, add new, create new | Implementation, architecture, patterns |\n73: | `fix_bug` | bug, error, fix, broken, debug | Decisions, implementation, errors |\n74: | `refactor` | refactor, restructure, optimize | Architecture, patterns, decisions |\n75: | `security_audit` | security, vulnerability, auth | Decisions, implementation, security |\n76: | `understand` | how, why, what, explain | Architecture, decisions, overview |\n77: | `find_spec` | spec, specification, find spec | Spec docs, architecture, overview |\n78: | `find_decision` | decision, rationale, why did we | Decisions, rationale, context |\n79: \n80: ### Learn Subcommands\n81: \n82: | Subcommand | Invocation | Description |\n83: |------------|------------|-------------|\n84: | (default) | `/memory:learn [rule]` | Create new constitutional memory (guided) |\n85: | list | `/memory:learn list` | Show all constitutional memories and budget |\n86: | edit | `/memory:learn edit <filename>` | Edit existing constitutional memory |\n87: | remove | `/memory:learn remove <filename>` | Remove constitutional memory |\n88: | budget | `/memory:learn budget` | Token budget status (~2000 max) |\n89: \n90: ### Search Subcommands\n91: \n92: | Subcommand | Invocation | Description |\n93: |------------|------------|-------------|\n94: | preflight | `/memory:search preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | Capture epistemic baseline before task |\n95: | postflight | `/memory:search postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | Calculate learning delta after task |\n96: | causal | `/memory:search causal <memoryId>` | Trace causal chain for a memory |\n97: | link | `/memory:search link <source> <target> <relation>` | Create causal relationship |\n98: | unlink | `/memory:search unlink <edgeId>` | Remove causal relationship |\n99: | causal-stats | `/memory:search causal-stats` | View causal graph statistics |\n100: | ablation | `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n101: | dashboard | `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n102: | history | `/memory:search history <specFolder>` | View learning history and LI trends |\n103: \n104: <!-- /ANCHOR:commands -->\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: <!-- ANCHOR:structure -->\n109: ## 3. STRUCTURE\n110: \n111: ```text\n112: memory/\n113: ├── README.txt      # This file, 4-command index and coverage matrix\n114: ├── search.md       # /memory:search - Unified retrieval + analysis (intent-aware search, epistemic, causal, eval)\n115: ├── learn.md        # /memory:learn - Constitutional memory manager\n116: ├── manage.md       # /memory:manage - Database management and ingest\n117: └── save.md         # /memory:save - Context saving\n118: ```\n119: \n120: No `assets/` folder exists for memory commands. Workflows are defined inline within each command file.\n121: \n122: <!-- /ANCHOR:structure -->\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: <!-- ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n127: ## 4. USAGE EXAMPLES\n128: \n129: ```bash\n130: # Save context to a spec folder\n131: /memory:save specs/007-feature-name\n132: \n133: # Retrieve context with auto-detected intent\n134: /memory:search \"how does the auth system work\"\n135: \n136: # Retrieve context with explicit intent\n137: /memory:search \"auth flow\" --intent:fix_bug\n138: \n139: # Recover from a crashed or interrupted session\n140: /speckit:resume\n141: \n142: # Auto-recovery mode\n143: /speckit:resume :auto\n144: \n145: # Create a constitutional memory (always-surface rule)\n146: /memory:learn \"Never commit API keys or secrets to git\"\n147: \n148: # List all constitutional memories and budget\n149: /memory:learn list\n150: \n151: # Check token budget status\n152: /memory:learn budget\n153: \n154: # View database stats\n155: /memory:manage stats\n156: \n157: # Scan for new or updated canonical spec documents\n158: /memory:manage scan\n159: \n160: # Force re-index all files\n161: /memory:manage scan --force\n162: \n163: # Check system health\n164: /memory:manage health\n165: \n166: # View learning history for a spec folder\n167: /memory:search history specs/007-auth\n168: \n169: # Capture epistemic baseline before a task\n170: /memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1\n171: \n172: # Calculate learning delta after a task\n173: /memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1\n174: \n175: # Trace causal chain for a memory\n176: /memory:search causal 42\n177: \n178: # Create causal link between memories\n179: /memory:search link 42 43 caused\n180: \n181: # View causal graph statistics\n182: /memory:search causal-stats\n183: \n184: # Run channel ablation study\n185: /memory:search ablation\n186: \n187: # View reporting dashboard\n188: /memory:search dashboard\n189: \n190: # Start async ingestion of multiple files\n191: /memory:manage ingest start /path/to/file1.md /path/to/file2.md\n192: \n193: # Check ingestion job progress\n194: /memory:manage ingest status abc-123\n195: \n196: # Cancel a running ingestion job\n197: /memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123\n198: ```\n199: \n200: <!-- /ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: <!-- ANCHOR:manage-subcommands -->\n205: ## 5. MANAGE SUBCOMMANDS\n206: \n207: The `/memory:manage` command accepts these subcommands:\n208: \n209: | Subcommand | Arguments | Description |\n210: |------------|-----------|-------------|\n211: | `stats` | (none) | Show memory database statistics |\n212: | `scan` | `[--force]` | Scan workspace for new/changed continuity artifacts and canonical spec docs |\n213: | `cleanup` | (none) | Remove orphaned or invalid entries |\n214: | `bulk-delete` | `<tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]` | Bulk delete by tier |\n215: | `tier` | `<id> <tier>` | Change importance tier of a memory |\n216: | `triggers` | `<id>` | View trigger phrases for a memory |\n217: | `validate` | `<id> <useful\\|not>` | Record validation feedback for a memory |\n218: | `delete` | `<id>` | Delete a specific memory |\n219: | `health` | (none) | Check memory system health status |\n220: | `checkpoint` | `create\\|list\\|restore\\|delete` | Manage named checkpoints of memory state |\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 338. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Memory Commands\"\ndescription: \"Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system including search, session recovery, constitutional memory management, database operations, and async ingestion.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"memory command\"\n  - \"memory save\"\n  - \"memory search\"\n  - \"memory learn\"\n  - \"memory manage\"\n---\n\n# Memory Commands\n\n> Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system across sessions.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/README.txt","text":"---\ntitle: \"Memory Commands\"\ndescription: \"Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system including search, session recovery, constitutional memory management, database operations, and async ingestion.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"memory command\"\n  - \"memory save\"\n  - \"memory search\"\n  - \"memory learn\"\n  - \"memory manage\"\n---\n\n# Memory Commands\n\n> Slash commands for managing the Spec Kit Memory system across sessions.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n\n- [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\n- [2. COMMANDS](#2--commands)\n- [3. STRUCTURE](#3--structure)\n- [4. USAGE EXAMPLES](#4--usage-examples)\n- [5. MANAGE SUBCOMMANDS](#5--manage-subcommands)\n- [6. TOOL COVERAGE MATRIX](#6--tool-coverage-matrix)\n- [7. FAQ](#7--faq)\n- [8. TROUBLESHOOTING](#8--troubleshooting)\n- [9. RELATED DOCUMENTS](#9--related-documents)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe `memory` command group provides operations for the Spec Kit Memory MCP system. These 4 commands cover context preservation, unified knowledge retrieval and analysis, constitutional memory management, and database maintenance plus async ingest. Session recovery now lives under `/speckit:resume`.\n\nAll commands interact with the memory MCP server tools (`mk_spec_memory_*`). They follow a gate-based argument validation pattern: if required arguments are missing, the command prompts the user before proceeding.\n\n### Canonical Section Order\n\nAll 4 memory commands follow a consistent user-first section order:\n\n```text\nGATE -> TITLE -> §1 PURPOSE -> §2 CONTRACT -> §3 QUICK REFERENCE\n-> §4 ARGUMENT ROUTING -> [MODE/WORKFLOW HANDLERS] -> ERROR HANDLING\n-> RELATED COMMANDS -> APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE -> [APPENDIX B+]\n```\n\nEverything above the `---` divider is for users. Appendices below are AI agent reference material.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:commands -->\n## 2. COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Invocation | Description |\n|---------|------------|-------------|\n| **search** | `/memory:search <query> [--intent:<type>]` or `/memory:search <subcommand>` | Unified retrieval and analysis: intent-aware search, epistemic baselines, causal graph, ablation, dashboard |\n| **learn** | `/memory:learn [rule] \\| list \\| edit \\| remove \\| budget` | Create and manage constitutional memories (always-surface rules) |\n| **manage** | `/memory:manage <subcommand>` | Database operations (scan, cleanup, tier, health, checkpoint, ingest) |\n| **save** | `/memory:save <spec-folder>` | Update packet continuity with semantic indexing |\n\n### Intent Types for Search Command (Retrieval Mode)\n\n| Intent | Trigger Keywords | Weight Focus |\n|--------|-----------------|--------------|\n| `add_feature` | implement, add new, create new | Implementation, architecture, patterns |\n| `fix_bug` | bug, error, fix, broken, debug | Decisions, implementation, errors |\n| `refactor` | refactor, restructure, optimize | Architecture, patterns, decisions |\n| `security_audit` | security, vulnerability, auth | Decisions, implementation, security |\n| `understand` | how, why, what, explain | Architecture, decisions, overview |\n| `find_spec` | spec, specification, find spec | Spec docs, architecture, overview |\n| `find_decision` | decision, rationale, why did we | Decisions, rationale, context |\n\n### Learn Subcommands\n\n| Subcommand | Invocation | Description |\n|------------|------------|-------------|\n| (default) | `/memory:learn [rule]` | Create new constitutional memory (guided) |\n| list | `/memory:learn list` | Show all constitutional memories and budget |\n| edit | `/memory:learn edit <filename>` | Edit existing constitutional memory |\n| remove | `/memory:learn remove <filename>` | Remove constitutional memory |\n| budget | `/memory:learn budget` | Token budget status (~2000 max) |\n\n### Search Subcommands\n\n| Subcommand | Invocation | Description |\n|------------|------------|-------------|\n| preflight | `/memory:search preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | Capture epistemic baseline before task |\n| postflight | `/memory:search postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | Calculate learning delta after task |\n| causal | `/memory:search causal <memoryId>` | Trace causal chain for a memory |\n| link | `/memory:search link <source> <target> <relation>` | Create causal relationship |\n| unlink | `/memory:search unlink <edgeId>` | Remove causal relationship |\n| causal-stats | `/memory:search causal-stats` | View causal graph statistics |\n| ablation | `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n| dashboard | `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n| history | `/memory:search history <specFolder>` | View learning history and LI trends |\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:commands -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:structure -->\n## 3. STRUCTURE\n\n```text\nmemory/\n├── README.txt      # This file, 4-command index and coverage matrix\n├── search.md       # /memory:search - Unified retrieval + analysis (intent-aware search, epistemic, causal, eval)\n├── learn.md        # /memory:learn - Constitutional memory manager\n├── manage.md       # /memory:manage - Database management and ingest\n└── save.md         # /memory:save - Context saving\n```\n\nNo `assets/` folder exists for memory commands. Workflows are defined inline within each command file.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:structure -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n## 4. USAGE EXAMPLES\n\n```bash\n# Save context to a spec folder\n/memory:save specs/007-feature-name\n\n# Retrieve context with auto-detected intent\n/memory:search \"how does the auth system work\"\n\n# Retrieve context with explicit intent\n/memory:search \"auth flow\" --intent:fix_bug\n\n# Recover from a crashed or interrupted session\n/speckit:resume\n\n# Auto-recovery mode\n/speckit:resume :auto\n\n# Create a constitutional memory (always-surface rule)\n/memory:learn \"Never commit API keys or secrets to git\"\n\n# List all constitutional memories and budget\n/memory:learn list\n\n# Check token budget status\n/memory:learn budget\n\n# View database stats\n/memory:manage stats\n\n# Scan for new or updated canonical spec documents\n/memory:manage scan\n\n# Force re-index all files\n/memory:manage scan --force\n\n# Check system health\n/memory:manage health\n\n# View learning history for a spec folder\n/memory:search history specs/007-auth\n\n# Capture epistemic baseline before a task\n/memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1\n\n# Calculate learning delta after a task\n/memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1\n\n# Trace causal chain for a memory\n/memory:search causal 42\n\n# Create causal link between memories\n/memory:search link 42 43 caused\n\n# View causal graph statistics\n/memory:search causal-stats\n\n# Run channel ablation study\n/memory:search ablation\n\n# View reporting dashboard\n/memory:search dashboard\n\n# Start async ingestion of multiple files\n/memory:manage ingest start /path/to/file1.md /path/to/file2.md\n\n# Check ingestion job progress\n/memory:manage ingest status abc-123\n\n# Cancel a running ingestion job\n/memory:manage ingest cancel abc-123\n```\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:manage-subcommands -->\n## 5. MANAGE SUBCOMMANDS\n\nThe `/memory:manage` command accepts these subcommands:\n\n| Subcommand | Arguments | Description |\n|------------|-----------|-------------|\n| `stats` | (none) | Show memory database statistics |\n| `scan` | `[--force]` | Scan workspace for new/changed continuity artifacts and canonical spec docs |\n| `cleanup` | (none) | Remove orphaned or invalid entries |\n| `bulk-delete` | `<tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]` | Bulk delete by tier |\n| `tier` | `<id> <tier>` | Change importance tier of a memory |\n| `triggers` | `<id>` | View trigger phrases for a memory |\n| `validate` | `<id> <useful\\|not>` | Record validation feedback for a memory |\n| `delete` | `<id>` | Delete a specific memory |\n| `health` | (none) | Check memory system health status |\n| `checkpoint` | `create\\|list\\|restore\\|delete` | Manage named checkpoints of memory state |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":338,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/README.txt","time":{"start":1780738267778,"end":1780738267782}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097f67dc23f6bf3a016a23e8dbabd08191ab7c128a5043011a"}},"id":"prt_e9c459a4c001lhEpDy1pvczLrP","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","messageID":"msg_e9c457a66001WeP7hi15ksnR2i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738267790,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hiSRiyxgWAqGVdAnfV3OLSwg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/hooks/pre-commit","offset":1,"limit":160},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/hooks/pre-commit</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env bash\n2: # Comment hygiene pre-commit gate\n3: # Blocks commits that add ephemeral-artifact pointers to code comments.\n4: # See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\n5: set -euo pipefail\n6: \n7: CHECKER=\".opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh\"\n8: REPO_ROOT=\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\"\n9: CHECKER_PATH=\"$REPO_ROOT/$CHECKER\"\n10: \n11: if [[ ! -x \"$CHECKER_PATH\" ]]; then\n12:   echo \"WARNING: comment hygiene checker not found at $CHECKER — skipping check\" >&2\n13:   exit 0\n14: fi\n15: \n16: VIOLATIONS=0\n17: while IFS= read -r file; do\n18:   full_path=\"$REPO_ROOT/$file\"\n19:   if [[ -f \"$full_path\" ]]; then\n20:     CHECKER_RC=0\n21:     \"$CHECKER_PATH\" \"$full_path\" 2>/dev/null || CHECKER_RC=$?\n22:     if [[ $CHECKER_RC -eq 1 ]]; then\n23:       VIOLATIONS=$((VIOLATIONS + 1))\n24:     fi\n25:   fi\n26: done < <(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACM)\n27: \n28: if [[ $VIOLATIONS -gt 0 ]]; then\n29:   echo \"\"\n30:   echo \"BLOCKED: $VIOLATIONS file(s) contain ephemeral-artifact pointers in code comments.\"\n31:   echo \"See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\"\n32:   echo \"Fix: replace the pointer with the durable WHY. Escape: add '// hygiene-ok' to exempt a line.\"\n33:   exit 1\n34: fi\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Comment hygiene pre-commit gate\n# Blocks commits that add ephemeral-artifact pointers to code comments.\n# See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCHECKER=\".opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh\"\nREPO_ROOT=\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\"\nCHECKER_PATH=\"$REPO_ROOT/$CHECKER\"\n\nif [[ ! -x \"$CHECKER_PATH\" ]]; then\n  echo \"WARNING: comment hygiene checker not found at $CHECKER — skipping check\" >&2\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nVIOLATIONS=0\nwhile IFS= read -r file; do\n  full_path=\"$REPO_ROOT/$file\"\n  if [[ -f \"$full_path\" ]]; then\n    CHECKER_RC=0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/hooks/pre-commit","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Comment hygiene pre-commit gate\n# Blocks commits that add ephemeral-artifact pointers to code comments.\n# See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCHECKER=\".opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh\"\nREPO_ROOT=\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\"\nCHECKER_PATH=\"$REPO_ROOT/$CHECKER\"\n\nif [[ ! -x \"$CHECKER_PATH\" ]]; then\n  echo \"WARNING: comment hygiene checker not found at $CHECKER — skipping check\" >&2\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nVIOLATIONS=0\nwhile IFS= read -r file; do\n  full_path=\"$REPO_ROOT/$file\"\n  if [[ -f \"$full_path\" ]]; then\n    CHECKER_RC=0\n    \"$CHECKER_PATH\" \"$full_path\" 2>/dev/null || CHECKER_RC=$?\n    if [[ $CHECKER_RC -eq 1 ]]; then\n      VIOLATIONS=$((VIOLATIONS + 1))\n    fi\n  fi\ndone < <(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACM)\n\nif [[ $VIOLATIONS -gt 0 ]]; then\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"BLOCKED: $VIOLATIONS file(s) contain ephemeral-artifact pointers in code comments.\"\n  echo \"See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\"\n  echo \"Fix: replace the pointer with the durable WHY. Escape: add '// hygiene-ok' to exempt a line.\"\n  exit 1\nfi","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":34,"totalLines":34,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/hooks/pre-commit","time":{"start":1780738267785,"end":1780738267789}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097f67dc23f6bf3a016a23e8dbabe88191964072bd0cec38d6"}},"id":"prt_e9c459a88001xJUuM6yl6bugwN","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","messageID":"msg_e9c457a66001WeP7hi15ksnR2i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738267802,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vywtuGJUKrc7DCHyzfV3KOHm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DOCTOR: MEMORY CONTINUITY-INDEX WORKFLOW (INTERACTIVE DIAGNOSTIC MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: role: Expert Operator running memory continuity-index diagnostics in interactive mode\n5: purpose: Read-only health check + drift detection with user review gates. No mutations. Report goes to packet-local scratch.\n6: action: Discovery → gate → analysis → gate → drift classification → recommendation → state log\n7: \n8: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n9: # OPERATING MODE\n10: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n11: operating_mode:\n12:   workflow: sequential\n13:   compliance: MANDATORY\n14:   execution: interactive\n15:   approvals: per_phase\n16:   tracking: phase_by_phase\n17:   validation: continuous_self_validation\n18:   intent: DIAGNOSE  # never APPLY in this YAML\n19: \n20: \n21: memory_doctor_invariant: |\n22:   Memory doctor is read-only by contract. It treats the active provider-keyed\n23:   profile DBs (ollama, hf-local, voyage, and openai profiles matching\n24:   context-index__*.sqlite) as the memory-owned stores it diagnoses but never\n25:   mutates. Rebuilds are owned by the /doctor:update orchestrator, which relies on\n26:   the per-file memory_index_scan transaction model so SIGINT uses the ~5 sec settle\n27:   window before restoring snapshots for cross-file consistency.\n28: \n29: upstream_assets:\n30:   contract: \"local command design contract\"\n31:   files:\n32:     spec: \"spec.md\"  # REQ-005..REQ-007 cover flock, snapshots, dashboard\n33:     decision_record: \"decision-record.md\"  # ADR-001 documents memory_index_scan tx model\n34:     tx_model: \"decision-record.md#adr-001\"  # per-file transactions + ~5 sec SIGINT settle\n35:     checklist: \"checklist.md#doctor-memory\"  # CHK-104 gold-battery acceptance bar\n36:   pass_policy:\n37:     minimum_result_count_per_query: 1  # existing memory gold-battery floor\n38:     post_result_count_floor_ratio: 0.80  # preserve current workflow threshold\n39:     recall_at_20_floor_ratio: 0.80  # preserve current Recall@20 proxy\n40: memory_doctor_philosophy:\n41:   principle: \"Detect drift before it breaks memory_search; this command never mutates — rebuilds run through /doctor:update\"\n42:   approach: \"Read memory_health + memory_stats → classify drift signals → emit recommendations\"\n43:   mandate: \"This command is read-only by contract.\"\n44: \n45: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n46: # USER INPUTS (passed from Markdown setup phase)\n47: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n48: user_inputs:\n49:   execution_mode: \"[EXECUTION_MODE] - INTERACTIVE (this YAML)\"\n50:   intent: \"[INTENT] - DIAGNOSE (this YAML)\"\n51:   incremental: \"[INCREMENTAL] - true|false (informational; no rebuild in this command)\"\n52: \n53: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n54: # MUTATION BOUNDARIES (READ-ONLY)\n55: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n56: \n57: field_handling:\n58:   defaults:\n59:     incremental_empty: \"false\"\n60:   incremental_policy:\n61:     true: \"diagnostic input only; recommend incremental apply when medium drift is detected\"\n62:     false: \"diagnostic input only; recommend full apply when high-severity drift is detected\"\n63: mutation_boundaries:\n64:   allowed_targets:\n65:     - \"mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite\"  # provider-keyed active profile DBs\n66:     - \"mcp_server/database/context-index*.sqlite.pre-doctor-memory.*.bak\"  # memory snapshot files only\n67:   forbidden_targets:\n68:     - \"<active-spec-folder>/**/*.md\"  # never write into spec packet docs from /doctor memory\n69:     - \"<active-spec-folder>/description.json\"  # spec metadata belongs to memory-save tooling\n70:     - \"<active-spec-folder>/graph-metadata.json\"  # graph metadata is not a memory doctor target\n71:     - \".opencode/skills/**/SKILL.md\"  # never edit skill bodies\n72:     - \".opencode/skills/**/graph-metadata.json\"\n73:     - \".opencode/agents/**/*.md\"\n74:     - \".opencode/commands/doctor/*.md\"\n75:     - \".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_*.yaml\"\n76:     - \"mcp_server/database/*code-graph*\"\n77:     - \"mcp_server/database/*deep-loop*\"\n78:     - \"mcp_server/database/*eval*\"\n79:     - \"mcp_server/database/*skill*\"\n80:     - \"mcp_server/database/*causal*\"\n81:   enforcement: \"This command is READ-ONLY by contract. No mutation phases exist in this YAML. Any attempted write halts with STATUS=FAIL and ERROR='confirm-mode-mutation-violation'.\"\n82:   validator:\n83:     name: validate_targets\n84:     runs: \"before any file write; diagnostic mode should never reach a write path\"\n85:     steps:\n86:       - \"For each target: resolve via realpath; reject absolute paths; reject paths containing `..` or symlinks escaping repo root\"\n87:       - \"Assert resolved target is repo-relative under repo_root\"\n88:       - \"Match resolved target against allowed_targets patterns only\"\n89:       - \"Reject any match against forbidden_targets patterns\"\n90:       - \"On first violation: abort, append violation to state log, exit STATUS=FAIL with diagnostic\"\n91:     on_pass: \"diagnostic reads may continue\"\n92:     on_fail: \"abort before any write; STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\\\"target validation failed: <path>\\\"\"\n93: \n94: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: # INTERACTIVE GATES\n96: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n97: interactive_gates:\n98:   before_phase_1_analysis:\n99:     prompt: \"Phase 0 complete. Continue to Phase 1? (y/n/details)\"\n100:     blocking: true\n101:     approvals:\n102:       y: \"continue to phase_1_analysis\"\n103:       n: \"STATUS=CANCELLED; emit state log with phase=phase_0_discovery\"\n104:       details: \"print Phase 0 discovery outputs, then ask again\"\n105:   before_phase_2_recommendation:\n106:     prompt: \"Phase 1 complete. Continue to Phase 2? (y/n/details)\"\n107:     blocking: true\n108:     approvals:\n109:       y: \"continue to phase_2_recommendation\"\n110:       n: \"STATUS=CANCELLED; emit state log with phase=phase_1_analysis\"\n111:       details: \"print Phase 1 drift classification outputs, then ask again\"\n112: \n113: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n114: # STALENESS SIGNALS\n115: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n116: staleness_signals:\n117:   embedding_drift:\n118:     detection: \"memory_health reports `embedding_health: degraded` OR records with `last_indexed_at` older than source file mtime\"\n119:     severity: medium\n120:   fts_miss:\n121:     detection: \"memory_health reports `fts_health: degraded` OR new spec-doc files not in FTS index\"\n122:     severity: medium\n123:   chunk_boundary_drift:\n124:     detection: \"Anchors moved or sections renumbered since last index\"\n125:     severity: low\n126:   trigger_phrase_drift:\n127:     detection: \"Frontmatter trigger_phrases updated but indexed alias rows stale\"\n128:     severity: low\n129:   embedding_provider_change:\n130:     detection: \"Vector DB rows with old provider id (voyage-2 vs voyage-4)\"\n131:     severity: high\n132:   divergent_alias_groups:\n133:     detection: \"Same canonical name routed to different record IDs\"\n134:     severity: high\n135: \n136: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n137: # WORKFLOW\n138: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n139: workflow:\n140:   phase_0_discovery:\n141:     purpose: Probe memory_health + memory_stats; capture baseline\n142:     activities:\n143:       - \"Run: memory_health({reportMode: 'full'})\"\n144:       - \"Run: memory_stats({})\"\n145:       - \"Bash: stat -f '%m %z' database/context-index__*.sqlite (mtime + size for present profile DBs)\"\n146:       - \"Interactive gate: before_phase_1_analysis\"\n147:     outputs:\n148:       - total_records: N\n149:       - last_index_at: ISO_timestamp\n150:       - fts_health: ok|degraded|missing\n151:       - embedding_health: ok|degraded|missing\n152:       - profile_db_sizes: [{path: string, size: bytes}]\n153:       - profile_db_mtimes: [{path: string, mtime: epoch_seconds}]\n154:     validation: discovery_complete\n155:     fail_fast:\n156:       - \"memory_health returns error → STATUS=FAIL with diagnostic\"\n157:       - \"Database file missing → STATUS=DEGRADED, message='index not initialized'\"\n158: \n159:   phase_1_analysis:\n160:     purpose: Classify drift signals + identify suspect records\n161:     activities:\n162:       - \"Cross-reference memory_health output with mtime: any spec-doc file with mtime > last_index_at signals staleness\"\n163:       - \"Sample up to 5 records flagged as drift candidates\"\n164:       - \"Run memory_drift_why per sampled record (read-only)\"\n165:       - \"Aggregate drift signals into drift_classes count map\"\n166:       - \"Interactive gate: before_phase_2_recommendation\"\n167:     outputs:\n168:       - drift_classes:\n169:           embedding_drift: N\n170:           fts_miss: M\n171:           chunk_boundary_drift: K\n172:           trigger_phrase_drift: L\n173:           embedding_provider_change: P\n174:           divergent_alias_groups: Q\n175:       - sample_drift_explanations: [up to 5 entries]\n176:       - severity_max: low|medium|high\n177:     validation: analysis_complete\n178: \n179:   phase_2_recommendation:\n180:     purpose: Translate drift signals into recommended action\n181:     rules:\n182:       - \"If severity_max == high (provider change OR divergent aliases) → recommend a full rebuild via /doctor:update\"\n183:       - \"If severity_max == medium (embedding OR fts drift) → recommend an incremental rebuild via /doctor:update\"\n184:       - \"If severity_max == low (boundary OR trigger drift) → recommend monitoring; rerun in 1-2 weeks\"\n185:       - \"If no drift → status=OK, no action needed\"\n186:     outputs:\n187:       - status: OK|DEGRADED|STALE|MISSING\n188:       - recommended_command: string\n189:       - recommended_when: now|low-activity-window|monitor\n190: \n191:   phase_3_report:\n192:     purpose: Emit packet-local report + state log\n193:     activities:\n194:       - \"Compose report following OUTPUT CONTRACT in memory.md\"\n195:       - \"Write to <packet_scratch>/doctor-memory-report.<timestamp>.md\"\n196:       - \"Print summary table to stdout\"\n197:     outputs:\n198:       - report_path: string\n199:       - status: STATUS_OK | STATUS_DEGRADED | STATUS_STALE | STATUS_MISSING\n200:     validation: report_emitted\n201: \n202: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n203: # OUTPUT CONTRACT\n204: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n205: output_contract:\n206:   format: markdown\n207:   required_sections:\n208:     - status_header\n209:     - database_state_table\n210:     - drift_signals_block\n211:     - recommendation_block\n212:   optional_sections:\n213:     - sample_drift_explanations\n214:   state_log:\n215:     path: \"<packet_scratch>/doctor-memory-state.<timestamp>.json\"\n216:     schema:\n217:       command: \"/doctor memory\"\n218:       mode: INTERACTIVE\n219:       intent: DIAGNOSE\n220:       timestamp: ISO_8601\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 233. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DOCTOR: MEMORY CONTINUITY-INDEX WORKFLOW (INTERACTIVE DIAGNOSTIC MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Expert Operator running memory continuity-index diagnostics in interactive mode\npurpose: Read-only health check + drift detection with user review gates. No mutations. Report goes to packet-local scratch.\naction: Discovery → gate → analysis → gate → drift classification → recommendation → state log\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING MODE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: sequential\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: interactive\n  approvals: per_phase\n  tracking: phase_by_phase\n  validation: continuous_self_validation\n  intent: DIAGNOSE  # never APPLY in this YAML\n\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DOCTOR: MEMORY CONTINUITY-INDEX WORKFLOW (INTERACTIVE DIAGNOSTIC MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Expert Operator running memory continuity-index diagnostics in interactive mode\npurpose: Read-only health check + drift detection with user review gates. No mutations. Report goes to packet-local scratch.\naction: Discovery → gate → analysis → gate → drift classification → recommendation → state log\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING MODE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: sequential\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: interactive\n  approvals: per_phase\n  tracking: phase_by_phase\n  validation: continuous_self_validation\n  intent: DIAGNOSE  # never APPLY in this YAML\n\n\nmemory_doctor_invariant: |\n  Memory doctor is read-only by contract. It treats the active provider-keyed\n  profile DBs (ollama, hf-local, voyage, and openai profiles matching\n  context-index__*.sqlite) as the memory-owned stores it diagnoses but never\n  mutates. Rebuilds are owned by the /doctor:update orchestrator, which relies on\n  the per-file memory_index_scan transaction model so SIGINT uses the ~5 sec settle\n  window before restoring snapshots for cross-file consistency.\n\nupstream_assets:\n  contract: \"local command design contract\"\n  files:\n    spec: \"spec.md\"  # REQ-005..REQ-007 cover flock, snapshots, dashboard\n    decision_record: \"decision-record.md\"  # ADR-001 documents memory_index_scan tx model\n    tx_model: \"decision-record.md#adr-001\"  # per-file transactions + ~5 sec SIGINT settle\n    checklist: \"checklist.md#doctor-memory\"  # CHK-104 gold-battery acceptance bar\n  pass_policy:\n    minimum_result_count_per_query: 1  # existing memory gold-battery floor\n    post_result_count_floor_ratio: 0.80  # preserve current workflow threshold\n    recall_at_20_floor_ratio: 0.80  # preserve current Recall@20 proxy\nmemory_doctor_philosophy:\n  principle: \"Detect drift before it breaks memory_search; this command never mutates — rebuilds run through /doctor:update\"\n  approach: \"Read memory_health + memory_stats → classify drift signals → emit recommendations\"\n  mandate: \"This command is read-only by contract.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (passed from Markdown setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  execution_mode: \"[EXECUTION_MODE] - INTERACTIVE (this YAML)\"\n  intent: \"[INTENT] - DIAGNOSE (this YAML)\"\n  incremental: \"[INCREMENTAL] - true|false (informational; no rebuild in this command)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# MUTATION BOUNDARIES (READ-ONLY)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfield_handling:\n  defaults:\n    incremental_empty: \"false\"\n  incremental_policy:\n    true: \"diagnostic input only; recommend incremental apply when medium drift is detected\"\n    false: \"diagnostic input only; recommend full apply when high-severity drift is detected\"\nmutation_boundaries:\n  allowed_targets:\n    - \"mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite\"  # provider-keyed active profile DBs\n    - \"mcp_server/database/context-index*.sqlite.pre-doctor-memory.*.bak\"  # memory snapshot files only\n  forbidden_targets:\n    - \"<active-spec-folder>/**/*.md\"  # never write into spec packet docs from /doctor memory\n    - \"<active-spec-folder>/description.json\"  # spec metadata belongs to memory-save tooling\n    - \"<active-spec-folder>/graph-metadata.json\"  # graph metadata is not a memory doctor target\n    - \".opencode/skills/**/SKILL.md\"  # never edit skill bodies\n    - \".opencode/skills/**/graph-metadata.json\"\n    - \".opencode/agents/**/*.md\"\n    - \".opencode/commands/doctor/*.md\"\n    - \".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_*.yaml\"\n    - \"mcp_server/database/*code-graph*\"\n    - \"mcp_server/database/*deep-loop*\"\n    - \"mcp_server/database/*eval*\"\n    - \"mcp_server/database/*skill*\"\n    - \"mcp_server/database/*causal*\"\n  enforcement: \"This command is READ-ONLY by contract. No mutation phases exist in this YAML. Any attempted write halts with STATUS=FAIL and ERROR='confirm-mode-mutation-violation'.\"\n  validator:\n    name: validate_targets\n    runs: \"before any file write; diagnostic mode should never reach a write path\"\n    steps:\n      - \"For each target: resolve via realpath; reject absolute paths; reject paths containing `..` or symlinks escaping repo root\"\n      - \"Assert resolved target is repo-relative under repo_root\"\n      - \"Match resolved target against allowed_targets patterns only\"\n      - \"Reject any match against forbidden_targets patterns\"\n      - \"On first violation: abort, append violation to state log, exit STATUS=FAIL with diagnostic\"\n    on_pass: \"diagnostic reads may continue\"\n    on_fail: \"abort before any write; STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\\\"target validation failed: <path>\\\"\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# INTERACTIVE GATES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ninteractive_gates:\n  before_phase_1_analysis:\n    prompt: \"Phase 0 complete. Continue to Phase 1? (y/n/details)\"\n    blocking: true\n    approvals:\n      y: \"continue to phase_1_analysis\"\n      n: \"STATUS=CANCELLED; emit state log with phase=phase_0_discovery\"\n      details: \"print Phase 0 discovery outputs, then ask again\"\n  before_phase_2_recommendation:\n    prompt: \"Phase 1 complete. Continue to Phase 2? (y/n/details)\"\n    blocking: true\n    approvals:\n      y: \"continue to phase_2_recommendation\"\n      n: \"STATUS=CANCELLED; emit state log with phase=phase_1_analysis\"\n      details: \"print Phase 1 drift classification outputs, then ask again\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STALENESS SIGNALS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstaleness_signals:\n  embedding_drift:\n    detection: \"memory_health reports `embedding_health: degraded` OR records with `last_indexed_at` older than source file mtime\"\n    severity: medium\n  fts_miss:\n    detection: \"memory_health reports `fts_health: degraded` OR new spec-doc files not in FTS index\"\n    severity: medium\n  chunk_boundary_drift:\n    detection: \"Anchors moved or sections renumbered since last index\"\n    severity: low\n  trigger_phrase_drift:\n    detection: \"Frontmatter trigger_phrases updated but indexed alias rows stale\"\n    severity: low\n  embedding_provider_change:\n    detection: \"Vector DB rows with old provider id (voyage-2 vs voyage-4)\"\n    severity: high\n  divergent_alias_groups:\n    detection: \"Same canonical name routed to different record IDs\"\n    severity: high\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n  phase_0_discovery:\n    purpose: Probe memory_health + memory_stats; capture baseline\n    activities:\n      - \"Run: memory_health({reportMode: 'full'})\"\n      - \"Run: memory_stats({})\"\n      - \"Bash: stat -f '%m %z' database/context-index__*.sqlite (mtime + size for present profile DBs)\"\n      - \"Interactive gate: before_phase_1_analysis\"\n    outputs:\n      - total_records: N\n      - last_index_at: ISO_timestamp\n      - fts_health: ok|degraded|missing\n      - embedding_health: ok|degraded|missing\n      - profile_db_sizes: [{path: string, size: bytes}]\n      - profile_db_mtimes: [{path: string, mtime: epoch_seconds}]\n    validation: discovery_complete\n    fail_fast:\n      - \"memory_health returns error → STATUS=FAIL with diagnostic\"\n      - \"Database file missing → STATUS=DEGRADED, message='index not initialized'\"\n\n  phase_1_analysis:\n    purpose: Classify drift signals + identify suspect records\n    activities:\n      - \"Cross-reference memory_health output with mtime: any spec-doc file with mtime > last_index_at signals staleness\"\n      - \"Sample up to 5 records flagged as drift candidates\"\n      - \"Run memory_drift_why per sampled record (read-only)\"\n      - \"Aggregate drift signals into drift_classes count map\"\n      - \"Interactive gate: before_phase_2_recommendation\"\n    outputs:\n      - drift_classes:\n          embedding_drift: N\n          fts_miss: M\n          chunk_boundary_drift: K\n          trigger_phrase_drift: L\n          embedding_provider_change: P\n          divergent_alias_groups: Q\n      - sample_drift_explanations: [up to 5 entries]\n      - severity_max: low|medium|high\n    validation: analysis_complete\n\n  phase_2_recommendation:\n    purpose: Translate drift signals into recommended action\n    rules:\n      - \"If severity_max == high (provider change OR divergent aliases) → recommend a full rebuild via /doctor:update\"\n      - \"If severity_max == medium (embedding OR fts drift) → recommend an incremental rebuild via /doctor:update\"\n      - \"If severity_max == low (boundary OR trigger drift) → recommend monitoring; rerun in 1-2 weeks\"\n      - \"If no drift → status=OK, no action needed\"\n    outputs:\n      - status: OK|DEGRADED|STALE|MISSING\n      - recommended_command: string\n      - recommended_when: now|low-activity-window|monitor\n\n  phase_3_report:\n    purpose: Emit packet-local report + state log\n    activities:\n      - \"Compose report following OUTPUT CONTRACT in memory.md\"\n      - \"Write to <packet_scratch>/doctor-memory-report.<timestamp>.md\"\n      - \"Print summary table to stdout\"\n    outputs:\n      - report_path: string\n      - status: STATUS_OK | STATUS_DEGRADED | STATUS_STALE | STATUS_MISSING\n    validation: report_emitted\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OUTPUT CONTRACT\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noutput_contract:\n  format: markdown\n  required_sections:\n    - status_header\n    - database_state_table\n    - drift_signals_block\n    - recommendation_block\n  optional_sections:\n    - sample_drift_explanations\n  state_log:\n    path: \"<packet_scratch>/doctor-memory-state.<timestamp>.json\"\n    schema:\n      command: \"/doctor memory\"\n      mode: INTERACTIVE\n      intent: DIAGNOSE\n      timestamp: ISO_8601","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":233,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml","time":{"start":1780738267798,"end":1780738267801}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097f67dc23f6bf3a016a23e8dbabf48191837ea84cc31f6c2e"}},"id":"prt_e9c459a8b0017eaZoLcd8D4aCT","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","messageID":"msg_e9c457a66001WeP7hi15ksnR2i"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780738268207,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c459c2d0015LhtcQr0bwYIFC","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fb3ced36c101b59758fd678ce817173dd5eaab7b","messageID":"msg_e9c457a66001WeP7hi15ksnR2i","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":148052,"input":10630,"output":165,"reasoning":41,"cache":{"write":0,"read":137216}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780738272537,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c45ad18001ajT1VbC35AD4vr","messageID":"msg_e9c459d9c001toKI1hF6VRlfWg","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","snapshot":"32b045a5a0f9c06b326c10cbba6e5ca299c00235","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738355253,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c461dc1001aZGHukKhCx5CSY","messageID":"msg_e9c459d9c001toKI1hF6VRlfWg","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","type":"text","text":"## Automation design\n\n| Behavior | auto-trigger | default-on? | self-maintaining mechanism | host vs new hook point |\n|---|---|---:|---|---|\n| `source_kind` tagging | Every write ingress: `memory_save`, `memory_update`, `memory_index_scan`, async ingest, feedback/system writers. Target: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts`, `memory-crud-update.ts`, `memory-index.ts`, `memory-ingest.ts`. | Yes | Server derives `source_kind` from caller/writer class, not user input; DB default/check constraint protects missing values; automated writers may only fill system-owned fields and cannot overwrite human/constitutional fields. | Needs pre/inside-write guard. `mutation-hooks.ts` is post-write only and too late for overwrite prevention. |\n| Idempotency receipts | Pre-mutation wrapper for retryable `memory_save` and `memory_update`; also proxy replay safety for retryable local daemon calls. Target: `handlers/memory-save.ts`, `handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`, `lib/storage/mutation-ledger.ts`, `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`. | Yes | SQLite receipt keyed by server-derived operation/content/request fingerprint; identical retries replay prior response, mismatched payloads fail closed; bounded pruning can run during retention/index maintenance. | Needs new pre-mutation hook point or transaction wrapper. Existing `mutation-hooks.ts` can invalidate caches after replay/write but cannot decide replay. |\n| Advisory near-duplicate | Post-save/post-index enrichment once embeddings exist; index scan repair can catch deferred vectors. Target: `handlers/memory-save.ts`, `handlers/save/enrichment-state.ts`, `handlers/memory-index.ts`, `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`. | Yes, if advisory-only | Deterministic threshold writes `near_duplicate_of` metadata only when vector exists; `last_dedup_checked_at` prevents rescanning unchanged rows; never hard-rejects. | Needs post-embedding/enrichment hook. `mutation-hooks.ts` can host a queue kick, but not synchronous duplicate judgment before embeddings exist. |\n| Feedback-event capture | Already auto-fires from `memory_search` and follow-on tool dispatch. Evidence: `handlers/memory-search.ts` logs `search_shown`, query flow, and `result_cited`; `context-server.ts` logs `follow_on_tool_use`; `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts` is shadow-only and default-on unless disabled. | Yes | Append-only-ish event table, feature flag `SPECKIT_IMPLICIT_FEEDBACK_LOG`, fail-safe writes, bounded in-memory query cache in `query-flow-tracker.ts`; no ranking mutation. | Already has hook points. Add reserved system-generated event/artifact type validation in the same ledger/write boundary, not manual reducers. |\n| Automated-mutation audit | Every automated mutation path: enrichment, reconsolidation, retention, tombstone, edge promotion, bulk delete, scan repair. Target: `mutation-hooks.ts`, `lib/storage/mutation-ledger.ts`, `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`, `handlers/save/response-builder.ts`. | Yes | Existing `mutation_ledger` is append-only via SQLite triggers; add stable event keys so repeated automated work records once or appends bounded attempts. | `mutation-hooks.ts` can host the generic post-write audit append if handlers pass actor, affected IDs, and reason. Some existing paths already append ledger rows and need dedupe, not duplication. |\n| Tombstone | Delete/unlink/retention surfaces: `memory_delete`, `memory_bulk_delete`, `memory_retention_sweep`, causal unlink. Target: `handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`, `handlers/memory-bulk-delete.ts`, `handlers/causal-graph.ts`, `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`, `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`. | Yes | First timestamp wins via COALESCE-style update; active/purgeable partial indexes keep recall and cleanup paths fast; retention sweep enforces expiry and records history/audit. | Needs delete-path transaction changes. `mutation-hooks.ts` can invalidate/audit after tombstone but cannot preserve first timestamp by itself. |\n| Stale-exclusion audit | Startup health probe, `memory_health`, `/doctor memory`, and scheduled maintenance. Target: `handlers/memory-health.ts`, `references/config/hook_system.md`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml`, `lib/search/hybrid-search.ts`. | Yes, read-only | Audit derives expected inclusion/exclusion from live query predicates; reports if default recall silently excludes deprecated/stale-but-relevant rows beyond intended policy; no fixture upkeep. | Not a mutation hook. Needs startup/health/doctor audit surface. |\n| Edge-promotion dedup | Auto edge creators: `memory_causal_stats` backfill, post-insert enrichment, spec document chain creation in `memory_index_scan`. Target: `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`, `handlers/causal-graph.ts`, `handlers/memory-index.ts`. | Yes | Natural key uniqueness over source, target, anchors, relation; auto edges skip or merge without overwriting manual `created_by`; bounded auto-edge caps already exist in `causal-edges.ts`. | Needs edge-store guard. `mutation-hooks.ts` can invalidate caches after edge changes; dedup belongs in `causal-edges.ts`. |\n| Tool-ownership lint | Pre-commit plus `advisor_validate`/`/doctor` diagnostics. Target: `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit`, `.opencode/commands/memory/README.txt`, `mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts`, `mcp_server/schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts`, `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md`. | Yes | Derive live tool list from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, compare command ownership matrix and allowed-tool frontmatter; no hand-maintained count drift. | Not a mutation hook. Best host is pre-commit and advisor/doctor validation. |\n\n## Zero-manual principles\n\n- Put every invariant at the writer/dispatcher boundary, not in operator instructions.\n- Prefer derived metadata over authored metadata: `source_kind`, ownership, stale predicates, and tool counts should be computed from runtime facts.\n- Make read-only audits default-on and fail-open; make mutating guards default-on and fail-closed only when data integrity is at risk.\n- Use append-only ledgers for automated actions, with deterministic event keys to avoid noisy repeats.\n- Run catch-up repair from existing maintenance loops: startup, index scan, retention sweep, `/doctor`, and pre-commit.\n- Keep 008 feedback reducers shadow-first: capture events automatically, but do not mutate ranking/retention until measured quality gates pass.\n\n## INTEGRATION ROADMAP\n\n| Phase | items | target files | automation trigger | UX touchpoint | exit criteria |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Phase 0 docs/scoping | Reconcile proposal numbering to the current `010` proposal; record that 008 is event-capture/diagnostics first; map each behavior to an automatic trigger. | `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md`, `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/research.md` | Spec planning only; no runtime trigger yet. | Operator sees one roadmap, not scattered manual chores. | Child 010 scope is provenance/idempotency/tool ownership/stale audit only; 008 active reducers remain deferred. |\n| Phase 1 provenance + audit | Add persisted `source_kind`; enforce auto-cannot-overwrite-manual; standardize automated mutation audit append. | `mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`, `handlers/memory-save.ts`, `handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`, `handlers/save/response-builder.ts`, `handlers/mutation-hooks.ts`, `lib/storage/mutation-ledger.ts` | Write ingress plus post-mutation hook. | Save/update responses can surface “automated fields skipped” and ledger warnings, like current mutation hook feedback. | All automated writes carry actor/source; manual/constitutional fields are protected; ledger entries are append-only and deduped. |\n| Phase 2 idempotency + near-duplicate | Add local idempotency receipt for save/update; add advisory near-duplicate metadata after embeddings exist; add `last_dedup_checked_at`. | `handlers/memory-save.ts`, `handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`, `handlers/save/enrichment-state.ts`, `handlers/memory-index.ts`, `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts` | Pre-mutation receipt wrapper; post-embedding enrichment; index scan repair for deferred vectors. | Duplicate retry returns replayed result; near-duplicate appears as advisory in save/search metadata, never as rejection. | Identical retry creates no duplicate row; changed payload with same key fails clearly; unchanged rows are not re-deduped. |\n| Phase 3 feedback event log hardening | Keep existing implicit feedback capture; reserve system-generated feedback artifact/event types; ensure batch learning stays shadow-only. | `handlers/memory-search.ts`, `context-server.ts`, `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts`, `lib/feedback/query-flow-tracker.ts`, `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts` | `memory_search`, follow-on tool dispatch, startup batch/shadow scheduler. | Search/debug profiles show event counts and shadow proposals without promising live rank effects. | Events are captured automatically; no user/agent forged system feedback enters reducer inputs; active reducers remain gated. |\n| Phase 4 tombstones + edge promotion | Make soft-delete first-timestamp-idempotent; split active/purgeable indexes; protect manual causal edges from auto promotion. | `handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`, `handlers/memory-bulk-delete.ts`, `handlers/causal-graph.ts`, `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`, `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`, `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts` | Delete/unlink handlers, retention sweep, causal backfill, index scan chain creation. | `/memory:manage` and `/memory:search causal-*` report “skipped manual edge” or tombstone state instead of requiring triage. | Repeat delete does not extend retention; auto edge promotion is idempotent; manual edge provenance is never overwritten. |\n| Phase 5 stale-exclusion + ownership lint polish | Add default-recall stale/status audit; add derived MCP tool-ownership lint; wire diagnostics into startup/doctor/pre-commit. | `lib/search/hybrid-search.ts`, `handlers/memory-health.ts`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml`, `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit`, `.opencode/commands/memory/README.txt`, `mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts`, `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md`, `references/config/hook_system.md`, `references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md` | Startup health probe, `/doctor memory`, `advisor_validate`, pre-commit. | Operators get passive warnings in health/startup and hard drift blocks before commit for ownership-map mismatch. | Default search exclusions are audited automatically; 37-tool ownership stays derived and in sync; no manual checklist is needed. |\n\n## Top risks + mitigations\n\n| risk | mitigation |\n|---|---|\n| `mutation-hooks.ts` becomes a dumping ground for policy that must run inside transactions. | Split hook phases: pre-mutation guard, transactional writer, post-mutation invalidation/audit. Keep cache clearing in `mutation-hooks.ts`; keep integrity decisions in write handlers/storage modules. |\n| Default-on automation silently changes recall or ranking. | Keep near-duplicate advisory-only and feedback reducers shadow-only; default-on writes can record metadata/audit, not demote memories. |\n| Audit ledgers become noisy and unactionable. | Use deterministic event keys, bounded retry counters, actor/source fields, and summary diagnostics in `/doctor`/health instead of raw row dumps. |\n| Auto edge promotion overwrites manual causal meaning. | Natural-key dedup must preserve manual `created_by` and evidence; auto can skip or add low-strength parallel evidence only if schema explicitly supports it. |\n| Stale/deprecated audit produces false alarms because deprecated rows are intentionally excluded today. | Audit should distinguish intended exclusion from “silent hard exclusion of relevant rows”; report as diagnostic until a policy decision changes recall behavior. |\n| Tool-ownership lint drifts if it reads docs as source of truth. | Derive from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS` and command allowed-tool frontmatter; docs are generated/validated outputs, not the authority. |\n\nDELTA_JSON: {\"iteration\":\"005\",\"focus\":\"automation-first design + integration synthesis\",\"findingsCount\":9,\"newInfoRatio\":0.78,\"impacts\":[\"source_kind tagging -> write ingress pre-mutation guard\",\"idempotency -> memory_save/memory_update receipt wrapper\",\"advisory near-duplicate -> post-embedding enrichment/index scan repair\",\"feedback-event capture -> memory_search and follow-on tool dispatch\",\"automated-mutation audit -> post-mutation hook plus mutation_ledger\",\"tombstone -> delete/unlink handlers plus retention sweep\",\"stale-exclusion audit -> startup health probe and /doctor memory\",\"edge-promotion dedup -> causal edge store natural-key guard\",\"tool-ownership lint -> pre-commit plus advisor_validate/doctor\"],\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/research.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/research.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/mutation-hooks.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-retention-sweep.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index-discovery.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/query-flow-tracker.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/mutation-ledger.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/causal-edges.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md\",\".opencode/commands/memory/README.txt\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml\",\".opencode/hooks/pre-commit\"]}","time":{"start":1780738301378,"end":1780738355251},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_070f6d96793fced0016a23e8fd4a84819194e49f8f47c97d20","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780738355739,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","part":{"id":"prt_e9c46f218001UC4MEI3jqLjt4S","reason":"stop","snapshot":"ed43334e8fd7781ab752d599b51084c23715ca37","messageID":"msg_e9c459d9c001toKI1hF6VRlfWg","sessionID":"ses_163bcc511ffeJbZHjaVz1S8sbA","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":158444,"input":6442,"output":3123,"reasoning":1423,"cache":{"write":0,"read":147456}},"cost":0}}
